<span id="freeTextContainer6300220337252511013">A belter. A great set of characters and dramas (Bumpass, Searcy... Stonewall Jackson) and never weighed down by the wonky military strategy stuff (which frankly I&apos;ve never got). Appropriately gory, profane and saucy. Sympathetic without sympathizing. I love that line from Cate about the blood of the young being the mortar that builds history. Marvelous.</span>
