<div id="review_3243245832" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3243245832" />
    <a title="Roger Taylor" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26044880-roger-taylor"><img alt="Roger Taylor" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3243245832?book_show_action=true">Apr 03, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Roger Taylor" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Roger Taylor" href="/user/show/26044880-roger-taylor">Roger Taylor</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3243245832" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14990117456641636562">This was a very enjoyable and interesting work of historical fiction which put a human face on one portion of the Confederate army during one year of the Civil War. Usaph Bumpass, the hero of the story is an enlisted man in the army of Stonewall Jackson during the period from the last phase of the Peninsula War, fought around Richmond, through the Battle of Second Manassas after which the Confederates headed north into Maryland and took part in the greatest one day battle of the entire war at An</span>
  <span id="freeText14990117456641636562" style="display:none">This was a very enjoyable and interesting work of historical fiction which put a human face on one portion of the Confederate army during one year of the Civil War. Usaph Bumpass, the hero of the story is an enlisted man in the army of Stonewall Jackson during the period from the last phase of the Peninsula War, fought around Richmond, through the Battle of Second Manassas after which the Confederates headed north into Maryland and took part in the greatest one day battle of the entire war at Antietam. The emphasis in the book is not about statistics or battle strategies but about the lives of the ordinary soldiers like Bumpass who endured the terrible privations of life on the march and the horrifying battles and the suffering caused by the terrible carnage that took place in those engagements with the enemy. This is a book that I can easily recommend to all interested in the Civil War. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14990117456641636562" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


